## Skill chaining diagram

```
workflow-build-feature
  └─ workflow-spec-tdd → test-unit → test-playwright → workflow-pr

workflow-fix-and-ship
  └─ debug-error → test-playwright → workflow-pr → deploy-verify

workflow-quality-gate
  └─ test-red-team → audit-security → audit-bundle-size → audit-performance → test-unit

workflow-launch-ready
  └─ enhance-web-seo → enhance-pwa → audit-bundle-size → audit-i18n
     → workflow-quality-gate → deploy-verify → iterate-post-launch

iterate-post-launch
  └─ debug-sentry-monitor → deploy-verify → test-playwright
```

## Rules vs Skills

- **Rules** (this file, `full-stack-ship-discipline.mdc`, etc.) = always-on policies, guardrails, routing
- **Skills** = activated on demand when a task matches the description
- Never put task-specific workflows in rules — they waste context on unrelated tasks
